WEBVTT

00:00.130 --> 00:02.826
Come on, come on, Captain,
pick up.

00:02.827 --> 00:04.994
Your friend Bob is secretly working
for Jimmy "the Butcher" Figgis.

00:04.995 --> 00:06.542
This is a call you're
gonna want to take.

00:06.543 --> 00:07.845
Bob must've done something
to him.

00:07.846 --> 00:09.432
Or maybe they're talking
about something super boring,

00:09.433 --> 00:10.968
like potatoes or beans.

00:10.969 --> 00:13.332
White rice, brown rice...

00:13.333 --> 00:15.500
those are just some
of the rices I love.

00:15.501 --> 00:17.345
- Mmm.
- Also basmati.

00:17.346 --> 00:19.911
- Mmm.
- Uh, that's all of them now.

00:19.912 --> 00:21.994
I should've known
Agent Whealon was dirty.

00:21.995 --> 00:23.619
There were signs.

00:23.620 --> 00:25.206
He wore a V-neck once.

00:25.207 --> 00:26.973
Bob.

00:26.974 --> 00:28.366
You did nothing?

00:28.367 --> 00:29.902
It's my greatest regret.

00:29.903 --> 00:31.740
Well, at least
he's still alive.

00:31.741 --> 00:33.960
When he comes out of the coma,
we'll get him to talk.

00:33.961 --> 00:35.715
Would you mind
getting us some food?

00:35.716 --> 00:38.689
I can't fathom eating these
candies that Peralta bought us.

00:38.690 --> 00:40.936
Chocolate is the devil's carob.

00:40.937 --> 00:42.832
And carob is Satan's raisin.

00:42.833 --> 00:44.755
I'll go down to the cafeteria,

00:44.756 --> 00:46.982
see if I can't scare up
some untoasted bread.

00:46.983 --> 00:48.428
Yum.

00:51.423 --> 00:53.190
Oh, Raymond.

00:55.732 --> 00:57.539
I forgot my wallet in my...

00:58.183 --> 01:00.907
Bob, you've killed him.

01:00.908 --> 01:03.145
And now I'm going
to have to kill you.

01:03.986 --> 01:06.087
I've never been more shocked.

01:06.088 --> 01:09.738
Sync & corrections by <font color="#00ff00">Rafael UPD</font>
<font color="#ffff00">www.addic7ed.com/</font>

01:09.739 --> 01:14.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:16.000 --> 01:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:26.108 --> 01:28.792
This is bad.
This is really bad.

01:28.810 --> 01:30.411
Where would Bob have taken Holt?

01:30.412 --> 01:31.812
I don't know, the library?

01:31.813 --> 01:33.447
Or an index card factory?

01:33.448 --> 01:35.449
Is there such a thing
as an accounting museum?

01:35.450 --> 01:36.717
- I...
- Hold on. I got this.

01:36.718 --> 01:38.819
I know the captain's
"find my phone" password.

01:38.820 --> 01:40.054
He's at the hospital.

01:40.055 --> 01:42.256
He's still at the hospital.
You're a genius!

01:42.257 --> 01:44.358
Well, I'd love to take credit,
but the truth is,

01:44.359 --> 01:46.092
life just isn't that hard.

01:46.128 --> 01:47.495
We got to get to the hospital,

01:47.496 --> 01:48.663
and we got to get there fast.

01:48.664 --> 01:50.030
- Then I should drive.
- Why you?

01:50.065 --> 01:52.466
I have nothing to live for,
and I drive like it.

01:52.467 --> 01:53.701
Okay, let's do it.

01:53.702 --> 01:56.003
[all screaming, siren wailing]

01:56.004 --> 01:57.371
[car horn honking]

01:57.372 --> 01:58.638
<i>Jake called.</i>

01:58.674 --> 02:00.241
We need to get back
to New York right now.

02:00.242 --> 02:01.242
No, no, no, no, no.

02:01.243 --> 02:02.510
You can't just leave.

02:02.511 --> 02:04.412
We may need some of those
contacts in the future.

02:04.413 --> 02:07.047
You're gonna go say good-bye,
and you're gonna mean it.

02:07.082 --> 02:09.316
So while I'm happy
the Supreme Court

02:09.317 --> 02:10.751
threw out my conviction,

02:10.752 --> 02:14.088
I'm also really sad
to be leaving all of you.

02:14.089 --> 02:16.690
Bethany, I know
you're an arsonist,

02:16.725 --> 02:19.694
but now it's time to set
the culinary world on fire.

02:19.695 --> 02:22.295
Sheila, you have the voice
of an angel.

02:22.330 --> 02:24.965
Whoever your next
music producer is,

02:24.966 --> 02:26.667
maybe don't stab him.

02:26.668 --> 02:30.004
Jen, you're a Nazi.
We never really clicked.

02:30.005 --> 02:31.806
Stay innocent, ladies.

02:31.807 --> 02:33.807
[cheers and applause]

02:34.810 --> 02:36.510
No, no, no.
What happened?

02:36.511 --> 02:37.912
He flatlined 20 minutes ago.

02:37.913 --> 02:39.713
The two men who were
in this room, where did they go?

02:39.748 --> 02:40.748
I don't know.

02:40.749 --> 02:43.050
- [cell phone dings]
- Okay, thanks.

02:43.051 --> 02:45.052
Gina said Holt
is still in the building.

02:45.053 --> 02:46.587
But where?

02:46.588 --> 02:48.756
I have to get into their heads.

02:48.757 --> 02:50.324
Whew.

02:50.325 --> 02:53.227
"Bob, what are you doing?"

02:53.228 --> 02:55.296
"I'm breaking the law, Raymond,

02:55.297 --> 02:56.564
"because I'm the worst.

02:56.565 --> 02:59.999
Now walk out of this room
as if nothing is happening."

03:01.436 --> 03:03.571
"You'll never get away
with this, Bob.

03:03.572 --> 03:05.406
"Jake is on his way.

03:05.407 --> 03:08.008
He's a great cop,
and he's going to save me."

03:08.009 --> 03:11.111
"Really?
He seemed so immature."

03:11.146 --> 03:13.881
"Yes, he seems that way,

03:13.882 --> 03:16.150
"but I know the real Jake.

03:16.151 --> 03:18.419
"He's like a son to me.

03:18.420 --> 03:20.187
"And when this is all through,

03:20.188 --> 03:22.656
we're going
on a road trip together."

03:22.657 --> 03:23.924
- Jake.
- Rosa, shh!

03:23.925 --> 03:25.259
I'm working on the case
right now.

03:25.260 --> 03:27.595
[snorts] That's weird.

03:27.596 --> 03:29.729
There's a smudge on this sign
right over the H.

03:29.765 --> 03:31.799
There's a smudge on this H too.

03:31.800 --> 03:34.268
Oh, my God, why would you
touch a hospital thing

03:34.269 --> 03:35.603
and then put it in your mouth?

03:35.604 --> 03:36.603
It's chocolate.

03:36.605 --> 03:37.872
Great instincts.
Never doubt yourself.

03:37.873 --> 03:39.206
Holt is trying
to send us a message

03:39.207 --> 03:40.808
using the candy bar I gave him.

03:40.809 --> 03:42.476
Just act natural, Raymond.

03:42.477 --> 03:43.611
Eat your candy bar.

03:43.612 --> 03:45.546
I can't.
It's disgusting.

03:45.547 --> 03:48.249
I don't care.

03:48.250 --> 03:50.384
<i>[tense music]</i>

03:50.385 --> 03:53.586
[sighs]

03:53.622 --> 03:54.688
H is for Holt.

03:54.689 --> 03:55.923
He's leading us right to him.

03:55.924 --> 03:57.124
Now all we have to do

03:57.125 --> 03:59.460
is follow the trail
of chocolate.

03:59.461 --> 04:01.028
This...

04:01.029 --> 04:03.264
this is why I became a cop.

04:03.265 --> 04:05.199
[sighs]
Charles, what took so long?

04:05.200 --> 04:06.767
I want to get out of this suit
before we take off.

04:06.768 --> 04:08.302
We're not going anywhere.

04:08.303 --> 04:09.570
The flight is booked,

04:09.571 --> 04:10.870
and there's already
a huge stand-by line.

04:10.906 --> 04:12.873
What?
We have to get on that plane.

04:12.874 --> 04:13.873
Were you stern?

04:13.875 --> 04:15.543
Amy, you know I wasn't.

04:15.544 --> 04:17.111
[sighs] I've got this.

04:17.112 --> 04:19.680
Holt's in danger,
and that lady's in my way.

04:19.680 --> 04:22.316
Never get between
a teacher's pet and her teacher.

04:22.317 --> 04:24.151
Ooh.

04:24.152 --> 04:25.419
Okay, vest lady.

04:25.420 --> 04:27.021
I don't care what
you have to do...

04:27.022 --> 04:29.657
Oh, you sweet thing,
you're pregnant.

04:29.658 --> 04:32.059
So pregnant.

04:32.060 --> 04:33.960
- What a miracle, right?
- Oh.

04:33.995 --> 04:36.429
Please give me
special treatment.

04:36.464 --> 04:38.833
I ripped her a new one,
and guess what fell out.

04:38.834 --> 04:40.367
Two tickets to New York.

04:40.368 --> 04:42.368
- Ugh.
- First class upgrade.

04:42.404 --> 04:43.636
Ahh.

04:43.672 --> 04:44.705
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:44.706 --> 04:46.106
No chocolate smudges

04:46.107 --> 04:47.508
in this entire parking garage.

04:47.509 --> 04:49.076
Or on floors one through five.

04:49.077 --> 04:50.544
We're officially lost the trail.

04:50.545 --> 04:53.581
Unless...

04:53.582 --> 04:54.949
No, that's not chocolate.

04:54.950 --> 04:56.250
- What is that?
- What?

04:56.251 --> 04:57.885
Don't eat it again!
[cell phone dings]

04:57.886 --> 05:00.054
Wait, getting a text.

05:00.055 --> 05:01.622
- It's Captain Holt.
- Where is he?

05:01.623 --> 05:02.623
What'd he say?

05:02.624 --> 05:03.991
"Inib rue tiid."

05:03.992 --> 05:05.092
Wait, I'm getting another one.

05:05.093 --> 05:06.927
"Ink obrvs whiz."
These are nonsense.

05:06.928 --> 05:08.262
He's been gagged.

05:08.263 --> 05:10.063
How would that come through
in a text, Scully?

05:10.098 --> 05:12.299
Wait a minute.
I know what's going on.

05:12.300 --> 05:14.834
He's secretly trying
to text us from his pocket.

05:14.870 --> 05:17.738
When I die, please
give Kevin my regards.

05:17.739 --> 05:19.240
What shall I tell him?

05:19.241 --> 05:20.506
"Regards."

05:20.542 --> 05:22.610
Scully, these look like
the weird texts you always send.

05:22.611 --> 05:25.412
Touch screen phones don't
respond correctly to my fingers.

05:25.413 --> 05:27.815
It's because I've been
electrocuted so many times.

05:27.816 --> 05:30.251
Hold on, I bet we can
reverse engineer this thing.

05:30.252 --> 05:31.552
Scully, type this
into your phone.

05:31.553 --> 05:34.420
"Inib rue tiid." Two "I"s.

05:35.557 --> 05:38.926
It came out, "Imm on rha rooj."

05:38.927 --> 05:41.328
"I'm on the roof."
He's on the roof!

05:41.329 --> 05:43.330
Oh, God bless you, Scully,
and your weird, dead hands.

05:43.331 --> 05:44.565
You and Hitchcock
are killing it!

05:44.566 --> 05:47.201
- [both chuckle]
- [grunts]

05:47.202 --> 05:49.503
- Oh, my God.
- Let's just go.

05:49.504 --> 05:50.971
Freeze! Drop your weapon!

05:50.972 --> 05:52.773
One more step,
and I kill your captain.

05:52.774 --> 05:54.308
Come on, Bob.
What are you doing up here?

05:54.309 --> 05:55.442
Why are you on the roof?

05:55.443 --> 05:56.977
Oh, my God.

05:56.978 --> 05:58.545
You're gonna zip-line
off of this thing

05:58.546 --> 05:59.847
like an American ninja.

05:59.848 --> 06:01.482
That is such a cool escape plan.

06:01.483 --> 06:03.150
Actually, I was gonna
throw Raymond over the side

06:03.151 --> 06:05.052
and make it look like
a bird-watching accident.

06:05.053 --> 06:06.520
Oh, please, do you think
anyone's gonna actually...

06:06.521 --> 06:07.755
It's genius.

06:07.756 --> 06:09.290
There's a red-tailed hawk roost
a block away,

06:09.291 --> 06:11.525
and I've got a pair of micro
binoculars in my pocket,

06:11.526 --> 06:12.726
like a fool.

06:12.727 --> 06:14.061
Okay, well, I stand corrected.

06:14.062 --> 06:15.962
Just drop the gun and surrender.

06:15.997 --> 06:17.097
If you turn on Figgis,

06:17.098 --> 06:18.632
this doesn't have to end
badly for you.

06:18.633 --> 06:20.567
You still have that file with
all the evidence against him?

06:20.568 --> 06:22.002
You mean the one you handed me?

06:22.003 --> 06:23.904
That was a good idea at
the time; we all thought that.

06:23.905 --> 06:25.339
Yes, that file's
in a safe place,

06:25.340 --> 06:26.607
and you're never getting it.

06:26.608 --> 06:28.208
Don't be foolish, Bob.
You're outnumbered.

06:28.209 --> 06:29.743
Outnumbered, my bottom.

06:29.744 --> 06:31.111
Figgis's men are on the way.

06:31.112 --> 06:32.713
Yes, I called for backup.

06:32.714 --> 06:34.548
Captain, down!

06:34.549 --> 06:35.649
[both grunt]

06:35.650 --> 06:38.484
Oh-ho, Terry took you down!

06:38.520 --> 06:39.619
Nice timing, Sarge.

06:39.654 --> 06:40.821
How'd you know we were up here?

06:40.822 --> 06:42.523
Captain marked
the Hs in chocolate,

06:42.524 --> 06:44.925
which I instantly connected
to the giant helipad H

06:44.926 --> 06:46.327
we're on right now.

06:46.328 --> 06:48.395
Oh. Cool.

06:48.396 --> 06:50.266
Cool, yes, we also solved that.

06:50.267 --> 06:51.460
Came straight up here
to the roof.

06:51.461 --> 06:52.945
We didn't wander around
even for a second.

06:52.946 --> 06:54.451
We're all smart.

06:55.648 --> 06:57.716
Smart.
This is a good hiding space.

06:57.717 --> 06:59.751
Scully, why are you lying down?

06:59.752 --> 07:00.752
'Cause there was a bed here.

07:00.753 --> 07:02.253
You took your shoes off.

07:02.254 --> 07:03.588
All right, look, a bunch
of sketchy, black SUVs

07:03.589 --> 07:04.989
just pulled up outside.

07:04.990 --> 07:07.258
Either it's Figgis's guys,
or Beyoncé stubbed her toe.

07:07.259 --> 07:08.860
Don't even joke
about that, Jake.

07:08.861 --> 07:10.862
That would be our new
number one priority.

07:10.863 --> 07:12.464
We have to call for backup.

07:12.465 --> 07:15.433
Figgis has people
in the NYPD and the FBI.

07:15.434 --> 07:16.534
So good luck with that.

07:16.535 --> 07:18.703
Wow, betraying the FBI
is one thing,

07:18.704 --> 07:20.071
but sarcasm, Bob?

07:20.072 --> 07:21.145
Wow.

07:21.173 --> 07:22.407
All right, we're on our own.

07:22.408 --> 07:23.808
We got to get Bob
out of this hospital

07:23.809 --> 07:25.008
and to a secure location,

07:25.044 --> 07:27.145
someplace the NYPD
doesn't know about.

07:27.146 --> 07:29.247
Captain, you're a grown-up;
let's just use your lake house.

07:29.248 --> 07:32.550
For the last time, not all
grown-ups have lake houses.

07:32.551 --> 07:33.852
We can go to my apartment.

07:33.853 --> 07:34.986
No one knows where I live.

07:34.987 --> 07:36.354
I thought you had Amy
over there once.

07:36.355 --> 07:38.021
Yeah, it was fun.
I moved the next day.

07:38.057 --> 07:39.390
Rosa's place it is.

07:39.391 --> 07:40.558
Well, they know
what Bob looks like,

07:40.559 --> 07:41.826
but they've never seen us.

07:41.827 --> 07:43.728
They think we're just
a big group of cops.

07:43.729 --> 07:45.897
What if we didn't
look like cops?

07:45.898 --> 07:47.832
<i>♪ I'm from New York,
I'm from New York ♪</i>

07:47.833 --> 07:49.267
<i>♪ I'm from, I'm from New York ♪</i>

07:49.268 --> 07:50.735
<i>- ♪ I'm from New York ♪
- ♪ Yeah ♪</i>

07:50.736 --> 07:51.936
- <i>♪ I'm from ♪</i>
- [sighs]

07:51.937 --> 07:54.139
Great, everyone looks fantastic,

07:54.140 --> 07:55.673
and our hats look normal.

07:55.674 --> 07:58.643
Wow, Sarge, you are just
stuffed into those scrubs.

07:58.644 --> 07:59.878
How do you do it?

07:59.879 --> 08:01.712
Exercise and diet.
It's not that hard.

08:01.747 --> 08:02.947
Eh, seems pretty hard to me.

08:02.948 --> 08:04.182
I don't think I'm gonna do that.

08:04.183 --> 08:05.583
This brings back memories.

08:05.584 --> 08:07.585
I loved playing doctor
as a child.

08:07.586 --> 08:10.388
The cancer has spread.

08:10.389 --> 08:12.223
Get your house in order.

08:12.224 --> 08:13.691
So we can sneak out like this,

08:13.692 --> 08:15.160
but what about Bob?

08:15.161 --> 08:16.694
Not to worry.
I've got that covered.

08:16.695 --> 08:18.596
Hitchcock.

08:18.597 --> 08:20.265
[mumbling]

08:20.266 --> 08:21.966
And, yes, he is bound
and gagged under there,

08:21.967 --> 08:23.701
but more importantly,
you said, "What about Bob?"

08:23.702 --> 08:24.769
That's the name of a movie.

08:24.770 --> 08:25.837
Holt made a pop culture
reference.

08:25.838 --> 08:27.038
All right, let's go.

08:27.039 --> 08:28.907
Okay, let's go over
our exit strategy

08:28.908 --> 08:30.175
one more time.

08:30.176 --> 08:32.177
Seat 2A is gonna need
help with her bags.

08:32.178 --> 08:33.678
She has twig arms.

08:33.679 --> 08:36.078
So if she blocks us,
I play the pregnancy card.

08:36.115 --> 08:38.249
And remember,
leave our luggage and...

08:38.250 --> 08:39.717
Roll the dice
with lost and found.

08:39.717 --> 08:42.053
I know; I've been studying this
map you drew on the barf bag

08:42.054 --> 08:43.386
for 40 minutes.

08:43.422 --> 08:45.056
Sorry, working is the only thing

08:45.057 --> 08:46.424
keeping me from worrying
about the squad

08:46.425 --> 08:47.859
and completely spiraling.

08:47.860 --> 08:48.860
Hot towels?

08:48.861 --> 08:50.128
For the billionth time, no!

08:50.129 --> 08:51.563
We don't want your boiled rags!

08:51.564 --> 08:54.599
[whispering] No, thank you.

08:54.600 --> 08:56.501
I don't know if it's
keeping you from spiraling.

08:56.502 --> 08:58.870
Look, why don't we just
take our mind off everything?

08:58.871 --> 09:00.938
We're in first class.
We get free movies.

09:00.973 --> 09:02.006
What? No.

09:02.007 --> 09:03.007
We can't enjoy ourselves

09:03.008 --> 09:04.209
while the squad is in danger.

09:04.210 --> 09:05.343
That's not fair.

09:05.344 --> 09:07.111
Amy, we're trapped here
for three hours.

09:07.112 --> 09:09.347
There's nothing else we can do.

09:09.348 --> 09:11.349
Fine, I'll watch a movie,

09:11.350 --> 09:12.584
but nothing we'll like too much.

09:12.585 --> 09:14.152
- No new releases.
- Of course not.

09:14.153 --> 09:16.087
We'll just put on whatever's
first alphabetically.

09:16.088 --> 09:18.021
[gasps] "27 Dresses."

09:19.425 --> 09:21.826
His cerebral blood circulation
is infarcted.

09:21.827 --> 09:23.561
Get me an ICP catheter, stat!

09:23.562 --> 09:25.063
Wow, that was amazing, Sarge.

09:25.064 --> 09:26.264
I watch a lot
of "Grey's Anatomy."

09:26.265 --> 09:27.865
That show's
surprisingly accurate.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.133
Yeah, the one episode I watched,

09:29.134 --> 09:30.601
there was a bomb
in the guy's butt.

09:30.636 --> 09:31.803
Oh, that's a good one.

09:31.804 --> 09:32.837
He's crashing!

09:32.838 --> 09:34.639
Push 10 ccs of corticosteroids,

09:34.640 --> 09:37.342
plus prep an ER
for surgical decompression!

09:37.343 --> 09:38.810
Look, I don't know
what any of this means,

09:38.811 --> 09:39.811
but I feel like Sandra Oh.

09:39.812 --> 09:41.246
Doctor, do you need me
to start a line?

09:41.247 --> 09:42.747
Oh, we're good.

09:42.748 --> 09:44.215
You said he's crashing.
Here's a syringe.

09:44.216 --> 09:47.484
Oh, good, I'll use this
to puncture his skin.

09:47.519 --> 09:48.820
Uh-oh, we got company.

09:48.821 --> 09:50.622
Uh, this man has
a bomb in his butt!

09:50.623 --> 09:52.056
We got to go.

09:52.057 --> 09:53.791
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:53.792 --> 09:55.627
Code silver, code silver.

09:55.628 --> 09:56.728
- [alarm blaring]
- Split up.

09:56.729 --> 09:59.529
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:02.190 --> 10:04.768
- [sniffling]
- You okay?

10:04.803 --> 10:06.704
Yeah, yeah.

10:06.705 --> 10:09.007
I'm just so into the movie,

10:09.008 --> 10:10.942
you know, really worried
about Katherine Heigl

10:10.943 --> 10:13.177
and her dressmaking business.

10:13.178 --> 10:15.178
I'm sorry, dressmaking business?

10:15.214 --> 10:16.748
Her architecture firm?

10:16.749 --> 10:19.150
- Her cupcake bakery.
- [sighs]

10:19.151 --> 10:21.285
The magazine she edits?

10:21.320 --> 10:23.855
Jane is the executive assistant

10:23.856 --> 10:25.957
to an outdoor
lifestyle entrepreneur.

10:25.958 --> 10:27.325
You're not even watching!

10:27.326 --> 10:29.327
I'm sorry.
I can't focus.

10:29.328 --> 10:30.728
I'm spiraling.

10:30.729 --> 10:31.796
Ugh, I knew it.

10:31.797 --> 10:33.498
If "27 Dresses"
doesn't distract you,

10:33.499 --> 10:34.998
nothing will, nothing will.

10:35.034 --> 10:37.802
So what do we do?

10:37.803 --> 10:39.202
We're gonna embrace the spiral.

10:39.238 --> 10:41.639
We're gonna talk
about these fears.

10:41.640 --> 10:43.641
Things are about to get real.

10:43.642 --> 10:45.209
- Excuse me, ma'am.
- Yes?

10:45.210 --> 10:46.544
We're gonna need
a box of tissues

10:46.545 --> 10:47.946
and some cozy blankets.

10:47.947 --> 10:49.247
- Okay.
- Oh, one more thing.

10:49.248 --> 10:51.849
- Mm-hmm?
- Y'all got sundaes?

10:51.850 --> 10:54.085
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:54.086 --> 10:55.853
[alarm blaring]

10:55.854 --> 10:57.422
- [bang]
- Oof!

10:57.423 --> 10:59.457
Nice.
Bedpan to the face.

10:59.458 --> 11:00.658
That's what this is?

11:00.659 --> 11:03.494
Ugh, I put my hands in it.

11:03.495 --> 11:06.531
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:06.532 --> 11:07.699
Figgis' men are everywhere,

11:07.700 --> 11:09.100
and now there's
hospital security

11:09.101 --> 11:10.101
at all the exits.

11:10.102 --> 11:11.602
- How are we gonna escape?
- Relax.

11:11.603 --> 11:14.505
There's a million ways to get
out of a hospital unnoticed.

11:14.506 --> 11:17.308
Name one.
[alarm blaring]

11:17.309 --> 11:18.810
- Dress up like babies.
- What?

11:18.811 --> 11:19.971
Well, you put me on the spot.

11:19.979 --> 11:20.979
Well, you brought it up.

11:20.980 --> 11:22.146
All right, wait, wait, wait.

11:22.147 --> 11:23.381
I've got a real plan.

11:23.382 --> 11:24.415
[cart rattles and bangs]

11:24.416 --> 11:26.284
- [groans]
- Hey!

11:26.285 --> 11:27.585
Go right!
Go right!

11:27.586 --> 11:29.187
Jake, Jake, Jake, Jake!

11:29.188 --> 11:31.155
Abandon gurney!
Abandon gurney!

11:31.156 --> 11:33.324
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:33.325 --> 11:34.459
Damn it!

11:34.460 --> 11:36.961
It's not Bob.

11:36.962 --> 11:38.596
Code silver.
Can't let you out.

11:38.597 --> 11:40.865
Look, you have to help me.
I'm an FBI agent.

11:40.866 --> 11:42.500
I am Serena Williams.

11:42.501 --> 11:44.002
I'm sorry.
They both suffer from

11:44.003 --> 11:45.303
grandiose delusional disorder.

11:45.304 --> 11:46.471
GDD.

11:46.472 --> 11:47.972
I've been taken hostage here.

11:47.973 --> 11:50.041
And I'm supposed
to be at Wimbledon.

11:50.042 --> 11:51.375
It's my serve!

11:51.410 --> 11:53.444
No, no, no, I am not crazy.

11:53.445 --> 11:54.979
Yes, he is, deeply.

11:54.980 --> 11:57.548
We need to transfer them both to
a secure psychiatric facility.

11:57.549 --> 11:59.449
Serena here just bit off
a doctor's nose.

11:59.485 --> 12:01.451
It tasted delicious.

12:01.487 --> 12:03.054
Yeah, you can go.

12:03.055 --> 12:04.856
No, no, call the FBI.

12:04.857 --> 12:08.264
No, call Venus!
Call Venus!

12:09.294 --> 12:11.227
Have a seat, Bob.

12:11.228 --> 12:13.296
Wow, Rosa.

12:13.297 --> 12:14.596
This is how you live?

12:14.632 --> 12:15.631
What were you expecting?

12:15.666 --> 12:17.033
I don't know, rock walls,

12:17.034 --> 12:19.102
weapons everywhere,
a waterfall for a door...

12:19.103 --> 12:20.769
I guess I was just
picturing the Batcave.

12:20.805 --> 12:22.338
Why do you need
a vase full of lemons?

12:22.373 --> 12:23.639
The room needed a pop of color.

12:23.674 --> 12:24.808
Who are you?

12:24.809 --> 12:26.042
All right, Bob,

12:26.043 --> 12:27.543
it's time to tell us
where that file is.

12:27.578 --> 12:28.978
And why would I do that?

12:28.979 --> 12:30.947
Because we are your only
chance of getting out of this.

12:30.948 --> 12:32.716
You have tons
of evidence on Figgis,

12:32.717 --> 12:34.217
which means he's probably
gonna kill you.

12:34.218 --> 12:36.853
If you turn on him, we can
get you into witness protection.

12:36.854 --> 12:39.189
You'll get a nice, little house
somewhere in Florida.

12:39.190 --> 12:40.790
I think you'd love Florida, Bob.

12:40.791 --> 12:42.992
I've never actually been there,
but Pitbull's videos

12:42.993 --> 12:45.095
make it seem muy caliente.

12:45.096 --> 12:47.864
I know Figgis, and you're
in far more danger than I.

12:47.865 --> 12:49.065
He's coming for you.

12:49.066 --> 12:51.401
And I guarantee his soldiers
find this place.

12:51.402 --> 12:52.435
Not gonna happen.

12:52.436 --> 12:54.070
I rent it out under
a shell corporation.

12:54.071 --> 12:55.071
Yeah.

12:55.072 --> 12:56.239
My mail goes to a P.O.
box in Queens.

12:56.240 --> 12:57.374
Yeah.

12:57.375 --> 12:58.608
My neighbors think my name
is Emily Goldfinch.

12:58.609 --> 12:59.843
Oh, yeah.

12:59.844 --> 13:01.177
People I work with all think
my name is Rosa Diaz.

13:01.178 --> 13:02.846
- Yeah... wait, what?
- Don't worry about it.

13:02.847 --> 13:04.080
- Okay.
- Enough.

13:04.081 --> 13:05.882
I'm gonna get this punk to talk.

13:05.883 --> 13:07.851
Oh, Bob,

13:07.852 --> 13:11.520
you are S'ed in the B.

13:11.555 --> 13:12.889
I can't lose Holt.

13:12.890 --> 13:14.124
I've barely scratched
the surface

13:14.125 --> 13:16.860
of the amount of approval
I need from him.

13:16.861 --> 13:17.860
Can I have your cherry?

13:17.862 --> 13:20.530
Oh, get in there, girl.

13:20.531 --> 13:22.832
And Jake... I haven't
seen him in weeks,

13:22.833 --> 13:24.934
and it's been so hard.

13:24.935 --> 13:26.803
I love him so much.

13:26.804 --> 13:28.104
Oh, my God.

13:28.105 --> 13:30.073
I've said "I love you"
to him before,

13:30.074 --> 13:31.941
but I've never added "so much."

13:31.942 --> 13:34.009
What if I never get
to say "so much"?

13:34.044 --> 13:35.111
What about me?

13:35.112 --> 13:36.112
What if something
happens to Jake,

13:36.113 --> 13:37.347
and he never gets
to meet my baby?

13:37.348 --> 13:38.681
I don't want to hang out
with some stupid baby

13:38.682 --> 13:40.016
who's never met Jake.

13:40.017 --> 13:42.585
Excuse me.
Two more sundaes.

13:42.586 --> 13:44.387
Oh, we've already
begun our descent,

13:44.388 --> 13:46.189
so we've suspended
our food services.

13:46.190 --> 13:48.024
Oh, I'm sorry.
Are we still in coach?

13:48.025 --> 13:50.392
Or are we in first class
where the rules don't apply?

13:50.428 --> 13:52.262
Charles, it's okay.

13:52.263 --> 13:53.496
We're about to land.

13:53.497 --> 13:54.730
You got me through the spiral.

13:54.765 --> 13:56.532
Oh, my God, you're right.
We did it.

13:56.567 --> 13:58.534
I am so sorry we yelled at you.

13:58.569 --> 14:00.437
But we will take
those sundaes to go.

14:00.438 --> 14:02.071
And I don't care if you
don't have a lid.

14:02.072 --> 14:03.839
Y'all make a lid.

14:03.874 --> 14:05.141
All right, here we go.

14:05.142 --> 14:07.210
Captain's about to lay into him.

14:07.211 --> 14:08.844
You need to tell me
where the file is.

14:08.879 --> 14:10.446
I'm sorry, Ray.
I'd rather not.

14:10.481 --> 14:12.148
Okay, not the dynamic start
I wanted,

14:12.149 --> 14:13.749
but I'm sure he's just
getting warmed up.

14:13.751 --> 14:15.083
I'd prefer not to ask you again.

14:15.119 --> 14:17.353
You sound desperate.

14:17.354 --> 14:18.555
I'm under your skin.

14:18.556 --> 14:19.856
The only things under my skin

14:19.857 --> 14:21.257
are oil glands, hair bulbs,

14:21.258 --> 14:22.425
nerve fibers, blood vessels,

14:22.426 --> 14:23.526
and a bit of fatty tissue.

14:23.527 --> 14:25.395
You forgot about
Ruffini's corpuscle.

14:25.396 --> 14:27.897
[laughing]
Oh, my God, you're rattled.

14:27.898 --> 14:29.598
Checkmate.

14:29.633 --> 14:31.667
I don't think that was
as vicious a burn as he thinks.

14:31.702 --> 14:32.902
You beat me.
It's over.

14:32.903 --> 14:35.070
I've lost all authority.

14:36.974 --> 14:38.173
Who's next?

14:38.209 --> 14:39.409
All right, Bob.

14:39.410 --> 14:41.878
You want to play hardball?
Good.

14:41.879 --> 14:44.246
Word on the street is,
you like jazz.

14:44.281 --> 14:46.216
I don't just like jazz;

14:46.217 --> 14:47.716
I'm fond of it.

14:47.751 --> 14:50.186
I don't understand
the difference.

14:50.187 --> 14:52.155
Tell me where the file is
right now,

14:52.156 --> 14:54.389
or I will ruin jazz
for you forever.

14:54.425 --> 14:56.058
I'd like to see you try.

14:56.093 --> 14:58.962
Wrong choice, daddy-o.

14:58.963 --> 15:01.563
♪ Skeeba-dee-skop-gop,
boo-ba-roppin jazz ♪

15:01.599 --> 15:04.167
♪ Jazzity-jazz, joozle jazz ♪

15:04.168 --> 15:06.936
♪ Jizz jang jingle jazz ♪

15:06.937 --> 15:08.671
What are you gonna
tell your kids, man?

15:08.672 --> 15:10.772
That their daddy's a crook?

15:10.808 --> 15:13.142
I don't have any kids.

15:13.143 --> 15:16.579
My whole thing was based
on you having kids!

15:16.580 --> 15:20.517
Now all of this
is gonna be hypothetical.

15:20.518 --> 15:23.520
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:23.521 --> 15:26.589
No tools, Diaz.

15:26.590 --> 15:29.359
All right, mister,
here are five stories

15:29.360 --> 15:32.728
about my cousin Lee-Ann
and her alleged Lyme disease.

15:32.763 --> 15:34.162
How's that gonna make me talk?

15:34.198 --> 15:36.232
Not everything's about you, Bob.

15:36.233 --> 15:37.834
I just needed to vent.

15:37.835 --> 15:39.301
God, you're such a Lee-Ann.

15:39.336 --> 15:41.204
All right, listen up, buddy.

15:41.205 --> 15:42.372
You're gonna tell us
where it is.

15:42.373 --> 15:43.673
And also what it is.

15:43.674 --> 15:45.341
We're a little unclear
what we're after.

15:45.342 --> 15:47.644
♪ Zwee-bop, zwee-bob,
Bob and the mob ♪

15:47.645 --> 15:49.012
♪ Mob-mob-mob ♪

15:49.013 --> 15:50.446
♪ Bob-Bob-Bob ♪

15:50.447 --> 15:52.348
No swords.

15:52.349 --> 15:55.018
So she's gonna look up at you,

15:55.019 --> 15:56.786
with hypothetical tears

15:56.787 --> 15:58.854
in her hypothetical eyes,

15:58.889 --> 16:02.859
and ask why all the other
hypothetical daddies

16:02.860 --> 16:05.762
came in for career day.

16:05.763 --> 16:07.529
I can't.
I can't.

16:07.565 --> 16:09.299
So it's like, "Yeah, maybe
you're tired all the time

16:09.300 --> 16:10.700
"because you're sick, Lee-Ann,

16:10.701 --> 16:14.036
or maybe you're depressed
because you live in Reno."

16:14.071 --> 16:16.438
♪ Ta-ta, ta-ta-ta,
ta-ta, dibbity-doo ♪

16:16.473 --> 16:18.641
♪ Cymbal-cymbal-cymbal-cymbal
cymbal-cymbal ♪

16:18.642 --> 16:19.809
What just happened?

16:19.810 --> 16:21.077
Somebody cut the power.

16:21.078 --> 16:24.270
Time's up.
Looks like Figgis found you.

16:26.440 --> 16:28.007
Okay, door's secure.

16:28.008 --> 16:29.358
That's the last of the candles.

16:29.376 --> 16:31.478
Is that multi-wick?
[sniffs]

16:31.479 --> 16:33.446
Am I smelling basil
and tangerine?

16:33.447 --> 16:34.881
It's called "Summer's Kiss."

16:34.882 --> 16:36.448
What the hell
is going on with you?

16:36.484 --> 16:38.317
I hate to rub it in, detectives,

16:38.352 --> 16:39.519
but I told you they'd find me.

16:39.520 --> 16:40.987
Sniper!
Everybody down!

16:40.988 --> 16:42.589
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

16:42.590 --> 16:43.823
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

16:43.824 --> 16:45.358
- Wrong guy! Wrong guy!
- Bob!

16:45.359 --> 16:46.758
[grunts] [glass shatters]

16:46.794 --> 16:47.894
Stay away from the windows!

16:47.895 --> 16:49.195
Captain, table!

16:49.196 --> 16:53.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:53.267 --> 16:55.101
Oh, my God.
What's going on?

16:55.102 --> 16:56.101
They tried to kill me.

16:56.136 --> 16:57.937
- [glass shattering]
- Argh!

16:57.938 --> 16:59.038
We have to get out of here,

16:59.039 --> 17:00.106
and we have to get
out of here now.

17:00.107 --> 17:01.507
It's cool.
I have a panic room.

17:01.542 --> 17:03.543
Yes!
There's the Rosa I know.

17:03.544 --> 17:04.776
"Summer's Kiss" my ass.

17:04.811 --> 17:06.079
But it won't fit all of us.

17:06.079 --> 17:07.646
Well, looks like Bob's
the odd man out.

17:07.647 --> 17:08.982
- Bye, Bob.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

17:08.983 --> 17:10.583
You have to take me with you.
They'll kill me.

17:10.584 --> 17:12.084
[glass shattering]
Look, I'll talk.

17:12.118 --> 17:13.785
The file is
in a safe deposit box.

17:13.820 --> 17:15.921
The keys are in my car
in the lining of my trunk.

17:15.955 --> 17:16.955
All right, fine.

17:16.957 --> 17:18.557
Take Bob with you
into the panic room.

17:18.592 --> 17:19.825
Rosa and I'll find
another way out.

17:19.859 --> 17:20.858
I'm sure you will, son.

17:20.895 --> 17:22.161
[gasps] You called me "son."

17:22.162 --> 17:25.198
No take-backs.

17:25.199 --> 17:26.432
How will I know
to open the door?

17:26.433 --> 17:28.134
When you hear me knock
the "Funky Cold Medina."

17:28.135 --> 17:29.969
I don't know what
the "Funky Cold Medina" is.

17:29.970 --> 17:31.638
Even context clues
have failed me.

17:31.639 --> 17:33.873
All right, you'll know it's me.

17:33.874 --> 17:35.258
[door clicks]

17:36.310 --> 17:37.677
Why'd you do it, Bob?

17:37.678 --> 17:39.811
Why'd you betray everything
you ever stood for?

17:39.847 --> 17:42.815
I spent 14 years bringing down
a Mexican cartel.

17:42.816 --> 17:45.151
You know what
they gave me for it?

17:45.152 --> 17:47.937
A letter of commendation
with my last name misspelled.

17:47.955 --> 17:48.988
In all fairness, Bob,

17:48.989 --> 17:50.690
who spells "Anderson"
with three Ns?

17:50.691 --> 17:52.859
Regardless, I figured
if they're not gonna give me

17:52.860 --> 17:54.826
any respect, I might as well
get paid.

17:54.862 --> 17:55.862
Was it worth it?

17:55.863 --> 17:57.463
Of course.
I made millions.

17:57.464 --> 17:58.631
I traveled the world.

17:58.632 --> 17:59.765
I've eaten whale.

17:59.800 --> 18:01.601
I always assumed whale
would be too fatty.

18:01.602 --> 18:03.036
Well, I don't have to assume.

18:03.037 --> 18:04.670
I know for a fact it is.

18:04.705 --> 18:06.339
It's disgusting.

18:06.340 --> 18:07.707
I threw up.

18:07.708 --> 18:09.675
[knocking at door]

18:09.710 --> 18:11.177
That sounds funky.

18:11.178 --> 18:12.911
Must be Jake.

18:12.947 --> 18:14.246
[door creaking]

18:16.350 --> 18:17.382
What's going on?

18:17.418 --> 18:20.352
Ha-ha, we fooled you, you fool!

18:20.387 --> 18:21.888
I was gonna do something cooler,

18:21.889 --> 18:23.456
but then I was just like,
"Go with what you feel."

18:23.457 --> 18:24.656
Who are these people?

18:24.692 --> 18:26.459
Oh, well, this is
my best friend, Charles,

18:26.460 --> 18:27.694
and this is my girlfriend, Amy.

18:27.695 --> 18:29.195
She's not really pregnant.

18:29.196 --> 18:31.030
We're taking things slow,
but it's going really good.

18:31.031 --> 18:32.198
- Jake?
- Right.

18:32.199 --> 18:33.816
They arrived about an hour ago.

18:33.834 --> 18:35.735
Sir, I'm gonna need you
to cut the power

18:35.736 --> 18:37.503
for Rosa Diaz in apartment 410.

18:37.504 --> 18:39.839
- 410 is Emily Goldfinch.
- Who?

18:39.840 --> 18:41.841
Curly black hair,
always smiling,

18:41.842 --> 18:43.408
a little chatty for my taste.

18:43.444 --> 18:46.012
I have so many questions,
but there's no time.

18:46.013 --> 18:47.880
Cut the power.

18:47.881 --> 18:49.716
<i>The sniper was Charles...</i>

18:49.717 --> 18:50.817
Bang.

18:50.818 --> 18:52.818
<i>And Rosa.</i>
[glass shatters]

18:52.853 --> 18:55.054
And while you were cowering
in the panic room,

18:55.055 --> 18:56.522
I went and got this file

18:56.523 --> 18:57.724
to make sure you weren't lying.

18:57.725 --> 18:58.925
Well, what happened in here?

18:58.926 --> 19:00.159
It looks like there was a fight.

19:00.160 --> 19:01.160
Oh, it was me.

19:01.161 --> 19:03.663
[banging and clattering]

19:03.664 --> 19:04.864
I was done with this place
the minute you all

19:04.865 --> 19:05.864
stepped foot in it.

19:05.866 --> 19:07.200
Oops.

19:07.201 --> 19:08.701
Guess you should have taken
our witness protection offer

19:08.702 --> 19:09.901
and gone to Florida, Bob.

19:09.937 --> 19:11.237
We have more
than enough evidence

19:11.238 --> 19:12.705
to take you and Figgis down.

19:12.706 --> 19:14.140
You've been played, Bob.

19:14.141 --> 19:15.508
It was all a ruse.

19:15.509 --> 19:18.411
You don't work with Jake Peralta
for three years

19:18.412 --> 19:21.381
without knowing what
the "Funky Cold Medina" is.

19:21.382 --> 19:23.182
Aw, hell yeah.

19:23.183 --> 19:24.851
I asked the guy,
"Why you so fly?"

19:24.852 --> 19:26.685
He said, "Funky Cold Medina."

19:26.720 --> 19:28.521
Both: Funky Cold Medina.

19:28.522 --> 19:30.989
Zero rehearsal.

19:31.025 --> 19:32.324
<i>[clinking on glass]</i>

19:32.359 --> 19:34.594
I just got off the phone
with the DOJ.

19:34.595 --> 19:37.363
They've arrested
over 75 of Figgis's men.

19:37.364 --> 19:38.998
His operation is decimated.

19:38.999 --> 19:40.299
[all exclaiming]

19:40.300 --> 19:41.383
Did they find Figgis?

19:41.402 --> 19:43.336
Not yet, but they're
confident they will.

19:43.337 --> 19:46.139
And when they do,
Detective Pimento can come home.

19:46.140 --> 19:47.206
Can't wait.

19:47.207 --> 19:48.674
I'm gonna eat his face off.

19:48.709 --> 19:50.343
You guys are so cute.

19:50.344 --> 19:51.810
I'd like to propose a toast.

19:51.845 --> 19:54.080
Even when Bob held
that gun to my head,

19:54.081 --> 19:55.314
I was not afraid,

19:55.315 --> 19:58.183
because I knew you
were on the case.

19:58.218 --> 20:02.021
I respect the hell out of each
and every one of you.

20:02.022 --> 20:05.491
Nine-Nine.
All: Nine-Nine.

20:05.492 --> 20:07.260
Love it when everyone
chants that.

20:07.261 --> 20:08.728
Mm.

20:08.729 --> 20:11.664
So Charles and I really
got into it on the plane,

20:11.665 --> 20:14.333
and around sundae number five,
I realized

20:14.334 --> 20:15.667
we should move in together.

20:15.703 --> 20:17.035
You and Charles?

20:17.071 --> 20:18.336
No, you and me.

20:18.372 --> 20:19.605
Oh!

20:19.606 --> 20:21.340
Yes, that makes
so much more sense.

